<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span></h2>
<p>There have been over 50,000 books published about the Civil War. It is often cited as the single subject with the most number of books published in the <a href="/entry/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>.</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Bibliographies">Bibliographies</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Eicher, David J. <i>The Civil War in Books: An Analytical Bibliography.</i> University of Illinois, 1997. <a href="/entry/Special:BookSources/0252022734" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0252022734</a></li>
</ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Histories_and_biographies">Histories and biographies</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Bedwell, Randall. <i>War is All Hell: A Collection of Civil War Quotations.</i> Nashville, TN: Cumberland House Publishing, 1999. <a href="/entry/Special:BookSources/158182419X" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 158182419X</a></li>
<li>Bush, Bryan S. <i>The Civil War Battles of the Western Theatre.</i> Nashville, TN: Turner Publishing Company, 1998. <a href="/entry/Special:BookSources/1563114348" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 1563114348</a></li>
<li>Coombe, Jack D. <i>Gunsmoke Over the Atlantic: First Naval Actions of the Civil War.</i> New York: Bantam Books, 2002. <a href="/entry/Special:BookSources/0553380737" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0553380737</a></li>
<li>Davis, Burke. <i>The Civil War: Strange &amp; Fascinating Facts.</i> New York: Wings Books (Random House), 1960. <a href="/entry/Special:BookSources/0517371510" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0517371510</a></li>
